#           Lightning Network payments backed by c-lightning (JavaScript/
#           Node, 557★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/ElementsProject/lightning-charge
# author : Nadav Ivgi (shesek) at Elements Project / Blockstream
# license: MIT
# npm    : `lightning-charge` (provides single `charged` bin)
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from bin/charged
# on the ElementsProject/lightning-charge tip — the `meow(usage, {flags:
# {...}})` registrations parsed exactly as declared, with the alias map
# preserved and the per-flag environment-variable bindings noted (charged
# auto-bridges every long-form flag to its UPPER_SNAKE_CASE env var via
# the envify pass).
#
# Direct deps from package.json (selected):
#   big.js             ^6.2.1   ← canonical JS arbitrary-precision decimal
#                                  library (this axis) — by Michael
#                                  Mclaughlin (MikeMcl/big.js); a
#                                  deliberately-minimal sibling to
#                                  MikeMcl's other libs `decimal.js` and
#                                  `bignumber.js`.  big.js focuses on
#                                  arbitrary-precision DECIMAL arithmetic
#                                  with full control over the decimal
#                                  scale and rounding mode (RM_DOWN /
#                                  RM_HALF_UP / RM_HALF_EVEN / RM_UP) —
#                                  exactly the toolset money/finance code
#                                  needs to escape IEEE-754 float
#                                  rounding pitfalls.  Used in
#                                  lightning-charge at src/lib/exchange-
#                                  rate.js for currency→msatoshi
#                                  conversion: BTC_MSAT_RATIO is
#                                  big('100000000000'), and toMsat
#                                  computes big(amount).div(rate).mul(
#                                  BTC_MSAT_RATIO).round(0, 3) (banker's
#                                  rounding up to nearest millisatoshi).
#   meow                       (Sindre Sorhus' tiny argv parser — the
#                              same parser that powers most Sindre tools)
#   express + body-parser      (HTTP server)
#   ln-service / lightning-client (c-lightning JSON-RPC client)
#   sqlite3                    (embedded invoice/charge DB)
#   superagent                 (HTTP client for exchange-rate fetching)
#   uuid                       (charge IDs)
#   ws                         (WebSocket invoice notifications)
#
# `charged` is the daemon binary; once running, the c-lightning data
# directory is attached via -l/--ln-path, the SQLite charge database
# lives at -d/--db-path, and HTTP requests are authenticated by the API
# token (-t) or random-token-persisted-to-cookie-file (-C).  Currencies
# other than BTC are converted to satoshis on the fly: USD/EUR rates
# come from Bitstamp, all other currencies route through CoinGecko, and
# the conversion math is done with big.js to avoid float drift across
# the satoshi → millisatoshi → invoice-amount conversion chain.  The
# RATE_PROXY / HOOK_PROXY / ALL_PROXY env-var trio routes outbound
# requests through proxies (useful for Tor or geo-restricted exchange
# APIs).  Webhook push notifications (`POST /webhook` registered out of
# band) fire on invoice paid/expired transitions.
